description:
&lt;p&gt;Surrey Heartlands CCG are looking for a Planned Care Programme Support Officer to cover maternity leave for the current post holder. The role will support the commissioning, redesign, programme management and development of a portfolio of priorities across planned care services within the East Surrey footprint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an ambitious vision for transformation and continuous improvement of health and care across our footprint. We are in the unique position of having secured a devolution deal, which for the first time really brings together health and social care by allowing us to commission from a single budget. We are also developing four dynamic and sustainable Integrated Care Partnerships (across East Surrey, Guildford and Waverley, North West Surrey and Surrey Downs localities) based on co-operation with our component partners, and focusing on local population needs, priorities and decision making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, we have responsibility, delegated from NHS England, for managing Primary Care contracts across the Surrey Heartlands footprint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key responsibilities of the role include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with mapping, and understanding the patient journey and care pathways;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with the development and completion of all Business Case and programme documentation;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support with the commissioning of service provision;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the review and development of service specifications, KPIs and information schedules;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Patients and public involvement, engagement and communication;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embedding of project management methodologies;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills to liaise with a wide range of health and care professionals;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organisational skills and the ability to be flexible in line with service needs;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A thorough understanding of confidentiality issues;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Show initiative, strong values and be people focused.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is an exciting time to work in the East Surrey planned care commissioning team with a large programme of work over the next few years as part of the NHS Long Term Plan. The work is varied and interesting with the opportunity to be part of improving services and the lives of people in East Surrey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post attracts a High Cost Area Supplement of 5% of the basic salary subject to a minimum and maximum payment per annum (pro rata where applicable) in line with Agenda for Change.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The job advertised is a full time post. However, flexible working arrangements and a secondment would be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would warmly welcome any questions about this opportunity - please contact Rebeka Pope, Programme Manager (details on the right), in the first instance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: due to the current COVID-19 situation the interviews will be undertaken virtually. Details of this will be shared with you should you be shortlisted for interview.&lt;/p&gt;
